cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is about image-to-image translation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed BiLevel (BiL) learning paradigm involves training two models, one at an instance-specific (IS) level and the other at a general-purpose (GP) level, which requires machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on human face and street view datasets, which are related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
